The council shall be comprised of the following members:
The secretary of the Energy and Environment Cabinet or his designee, who shall serve ex officio;
The director of the Division of Forestry or his designee;
The chairman of the University of Kentucky Department of Forestry or his designee;
The chairman of the Kentucky Soil and Water Conservation Commission or his designee;
A representative of the Kentucky Forest Industries Association appointed by the Governor;
A representative of the primary wood products industry appointed by the Governor;
A representative of the secondary wood products industry appointed by the Governor;
A representative of the Kentucky Farm Bureau Federation appointed by the Governor;
A certified tree farmer or forest steward appointed by the Governor;
A representative of the Kentucky paper products industry appointed by the Governor; and
Two representatives of public interest groups active in natural resource conservation or environmental protection issues appointed by the Governor from three (3) nominees, one (1) from the Cumberland Chapter of the Sierra Club, one (1) from the Kentucky Resources Council; and one (1) from Kentuckians for the Commonwealth.
